text: Bisu or BISU may refer to: * Bisu (festival), a festival celebrated in South Canara region in Karnataka and Kerala as New year, India *Bisu (marque), a Chinese automotive brand. * Beijing International Studies University, a Chinese university in Chaoyang District, Beijing, China * Bohol Island State University, a public university in the Philippines * Bes or Bisu, an Egyptian deity * Bisu, the alias of Kim Taek-Yong (born 1989), professional StarCraft player from South Korea * Bisu language, a language of the Sino-Tibetan family * Ingrid Bisu (born 1987), actress and producer
title: Bisu
